    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The current recommended way to do that is using [`connectHits`](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/react/connectors/connectHits.html), which has an example doing just that ([link](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/react/guide/Conditional_display.html))\r\n\r\nBasically that’s this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst content = createConnector({\r\n    displayName: 'ConditionalResults',\r\n    getProvidedProps(props, searchState, searchResults) {\r\n      const noResults = searchResults.results ? searchResults.results.nbHits === 0 : false;\r\n      return {query: searchState.query, noResults};\r\n    },\r\n })(({noResults, query}) => {\r\n    const content = noResults\r\n      ? <div>No results found for {query}</div>\r\n      : <div>Some results</div>;\r\n    return <div>{content}</div>;\r\n });\r\n```",
    "created_at": "2017-03-06T18:52:02Z",
